<HEADLINE>
<P>
LESS TRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I have just recently returned from a camping trip in Anzo Borrego State Park 
and I am happy to say that for the first time in many years I have not had to 
pick up the trash of other careless campers. Usually when I go I bring a trash 
bag for my own refuse and another one for the garbage that other people have 
left behind. 
</P>
<P>
I take it as a good sign that people are finally becoming aware of how delicate 
nature is and that we should live with nature, in harmony, and not against it. 
</P>
<P>
PAUL JURGENS 
</P>
<P>
La Mesa 
</P>
</TEXT>
