</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rehema Stephens scored 24 points and Sandra Van Embricqs added 22 as UCLA beat 
USC, 76-72, Thursday night in a Pacific 10 Conference women's basketball game 
at Pauley Pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
With the victory, UCLA (17-11, 12-6 in the Pac-10) clinched third place in the 
conference and may have wrapped up a berth in the NCAA tournament. Pairings for 
the NCAA tournament will be announced Sunday. 
</P>
