<P>
REDHAIR'S KEY THREE-POINT BASKETS LEAD ASU OVER WASHINGTON, 57-51 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TEMPE, Ariz. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mike Redhair scored a career-high 18 points Thursday night, leading Arizona 
State to a 57-51 victory over Washington in the first round of the Pacific 10 
Conference tournament at Arizona State. 
</P>
<P>
A senior guard from Tucson, Redhair made only six of 16 shots, including five 
of a tournament-record 14 three-point attempts, but nailed two three-pointers 
to spark a 10-0 run that lifted ASU in the last 2:01, propelling the Sun Devils 
(14-14) into a quarterfinal game today against top-seeded Oregon State (22-5). 
</P>
<P>
Center Doug West scored 17 points to lead Washington (11-17), which played 
without three-time all-conference guard Eldridge Recasner, who was in New 
Orleans to attend his grandfather's funeral. 
</P>
<P>
Doug Meekins, formerly of Crenshaw High, scored 13 points for Washington, and 
Dion Brown, also from Crenshaw, had 12 points and 11 rebounds. JERRY CROWE 
</P>
