<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP BASKETBALL STATE PLAYOFFS; 
</P>
<P>
DIVISION IV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM HAMILTON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Clara 77, Laguna Beach 48 -- After a 140-mile trip to Ventura College, 
the Artists never got on track and lost to the defending state champions. 
</P>
<P>
Laguna Beach (23-7) went 11 minutes 30 seconds from the end of the first 
quarter until the opening minutes of the third quarter without scoring a field 
goal and fell behind, 38-12. 
</P>
<P>
Guard Shon Tarver scored Santa Clara's first 12 points and then put on a show, 
scoring 39 points on a variety of drives, dunks and three-point shots. 
</P>
<P>
Tarver, who has narrowed his college choices to Notre Dame, Nevada Las Vegas, 
UCLA, Syracuse and Georgia Tech, made 15 of 24 shots and was five of eight at 
the free-throw line. Tarver's final basket was his most spectacular, a dunk off 
an alley-oop pass before he left the game with 4:19 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Clara (26-0), which hasn't lost a game since losing to Huntington Beach 
Edison in December of 1988, won its 32nd in a row. TOM HAMILTON 
</P>
</TEXT>
