<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: THREE SECTION PLAYERS ON SHRINE FOOTBALL TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Three San Diego Section players have been named to the Shrine Football South 
team, and three others have been named as alternates. 
</P>
<P>
The first-team picks are defensive lineman Dereke Fleming (6-feet-4, 230 
pounds) of Mission Bay, defensive lineman Sale Isaia (6-6, 260) of Oceanside 
and defensive back John McCartney (6-2, 190) of Lincoln. 
</P>
<P>
The alternates are wide receiver J.J. Stokes (6-5, 200) of Point Loma, 
quarterback Dan White (6-4, 205) of Point Loma and linebacker Pulu Poumele 
(6-3, 240) of Oceanside. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Christian Heritage College will play its National Christian Collegiate Athletic 
Assn. playoff game against The Master's College at Point Loma Nazarene Saturday 
at 7:30 p.m., the school announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
The winner will advance to the NCCAA tournament at Chattanooga, Tenn., next 
Thursday through Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
The Hawks, ranked No. 1 in the NCCAA most of the season, were upset by Southern 
California College in the NAIA District 3 championship game Saturday night. 
Christian Heritage (29-6) was the district's top seed. 
</P>
<P>
MEN'S VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Eric Etebari and Mike Mattarocci had 21 kills apiece as No. 8 San Diego State 
defeated No. 9 Ball State, 13-15, 16-14, 15-3, 15-10 in a nonconference match 
at Peterson Gym. SDSU is 12-9, Ball State 15-6. 
</P>
<P>
SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
The University of San Diego allowed 16 hits and committed six errors in a 7-5 
loss to Southern California College. USD (5-4) rallied for three runs in the 
sixth and seventh innings. 
</P>
