<P>
BOY SET ALIGHT BY BULLY FIGHTS FOR LIFE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
David Aupont spent his 12th birthday fighting for his life in a New York City 
hospital after a bully allegedly beat him with a bat, tied him up, soaked him 
with gasoline and set him afire in a garage because he refused to smoke crack. 
While David couldn't celebrate, former President Ronald Reagan, the White House 
and Mayor David N. Dinkins were among well-wishers who showered him with cards, 
gifts, balloons, flowers and messages, a hospital spokeswoman said. A suspect 
just a year older than David was arrested and charged in the attack. 
