<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: NAMES IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ned Fowler, who resigned as Tulane basketball coach in the wake of a 
point-shaving scandal in 1985, was named basketball coach at Stephen F. Austin 
University. 
</P>
<P>
Fowler's resignation followed accusations by an Orleans Parish grand jury that 
five Tulane players had rigged the outcome of at least two games during the 
1984-85 season. 
</P>
<P>
Fowler disclaimed knowledge of point-shaving when he left Tulane, which 
canceled its basketball program because of the scandal. 
</P>
<P>
Tulane returned to Metro Conference play this season after its self-imposed, 
four-year ban. 
</P>
