<HEADLINE>
<P>
EL CAMINO REAL PROVES RANKING WELL DESERVED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRIAN MURPHY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
When one ponders El Camino Real High's 18-1 dismantling of host Taft in a West 
Valley League opener Thursday, several things leap to the fore. 
</P>
<P>
There was the razor-sharp pitching of senior right-hander Patrick Treend (1-0), 
who scattered just three hits -- two of them infield singles -- and allowed no 
earned runs in going the distance. 
</P>
<P>
There were the pyrotechnics provided by senior first baseman Ryan McGuire and 
senior catcher Bobby Kim, each of whom rapped out three hits, a home run and 
drove in four runs. 
</P>
<P>
And there was sparkling defense, as El Camino Real third baseman Greg Lederman 
showed range and arm strength, McGuire dropped into the splits digging out 
throws and right fielder Chris Castillo sprawled across the outfield grass to 
make a diving catch. 
</P>
<P>
In sum, a solid all-around performance. 
</P>
<P>
"We did play awfully well today," McGuire conceded. "We'd be hard-pressed to 
play this well all year." 
</P>
<P>
It wasn't bad for an opener, though. 
</P>
<P>
But these guys aren't robots. In fact, they could be heard 'fessing up to 
having pregame nerves. After all, the unanimous pick for No. 1 in the Valley, 
the Conquistadores had yet to play a game. 
</P>
<P>
"Today, actually, I was really nervous," Treend said. "Coming in here 0-0, most 
of us were a little worried about how it might come out." 
</P>
<P>
Not to worry. After McGuire and Jason Cohen knocked in runs in the top of the 
first for a 2-0 lead, El Camino Real scored four more in the third on a two-run 
McGuire homer to right and a single by Kim that chased loser Cory Jacobson. 
</P>
<P>
Seven more runs followed in the fourth as 12 Conquistadores batted and the roof 
caved in for Taft (3-1, 0-1). 
</P>
<P>
For El Camino Real, center-fielder Jeff Marks had three hits, including a 
double, and drove in two runs. 
</P>
<P>
Treend struck out seven and walked just one. 
</P>
</TEXT>
