AGOURA'S SILVERMAN ACCEPTS OKLAHOMA TENNIS SCHOLARSHIP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Agoura High senior Trisha Silverman has orally accepted a tennis scholarship 
offer from the University of Oklahoma. 
</P>
<P>
Silverman, ranked sixth by the United States Tennis Assn. in girls' 
18-and-under singles, also considered offers from Michigan, Northwestern, North 
Carolina and UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Silverman lost in the Southern Section quarterfinals last year and has led 
Agoura to three consecutive Frontier League titles. Agoura has advanced to the 
3-A Division semifinals three consecutive years. 
</P>
<P>
Silverman intends to major in motion picture and film studies at Oklahoma. 
</P>
<P>
Athletes can officially sign letters of intent beginning April 1. 
</P>
