<P>
SUNDAY CELEBRITY GAME TO HONOR GATHERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Black Student Assn. of Loyola Marymount will sponsor a celebrity basketball 
game at 2 p.m. Sunday in Gersten Pavilion. The game will be dedicated to Hank 
Gathers, who was scheduled to be an announcer for the game and was a member of 
the association. 
</P>
<P>
Those expected to play in the game include actor Richard Roundtree, Rams 
running back Greg Bell and Stoney Jackson from the cast of "227." 
</P>
<P>
Loyola Marymount volleyball Coach Mike Normand announced the signing of four 
players for the women's team this week. The signees are Teri Runge, a 5-foot-11 
middle blocker from Coeur d'Alene, Idaho, who was all-state in volleyball and 
basketball, 5-11 middle blocker Lisa Wenker from El Camino College, 5-9 outside 
hitter Deanna Doolittle from Woodbridge High in Irvine and 5-9 outside hitter 
Shawna Mickartz from Irvine High. Doolittle and Mickartz also play together on 
the Orange County Volleyball Club. 
</P>
<P>
John Shearer of Manhattan Beach, a three-time men's senior world champion, 
easily won the over-30 division of the first Manhattan Beach Bodyboarding 
Championships last weekend. Over 120 competitors braved rain, wind and four- to 
six-foot waves at the city pier. 
