Capt. Robert Prouse, 51, of Conyers, Ga.; First Officer Robert Kirchner, 35, of 
Highland Ranch, Colo., and Second Officer Joseph Balzer, 34, of Antioch, Tenn., 
voluntarily provided blood samples to investigators and were released. 
</P>
<P>
Alan Muncaster, an airline spokesman, said the results of the tests will not be 
known for several days. "Until we have those results, the pilots have been 
removed from service," Muncaster said. 
