<HEADLINE>
<P>
POP LP CHART: IT'S ABDUL AND JACKSON, AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ever get the feeling that three months from now Paula Abdul and Janet Jackson 
will still be 1-2 on the Billboard magazine pop album chart? That's the way 
it's been for weeks, though the fact that Jackson has the No. 1 pop single -- 
"Escapade" -- should change things in her favor one of these weeks. Michael 
Bolton's "Soul Provider" -- boosted by hit singles -- moved up three notches to 
No. 6. 
</P>
<P>
Bonnie Raitt is still basking in the afterglow of her Grammy victories. Her 
"Nick of Time" album jumped 10 more places, to No. 12. Speaking of Grammys, the 
"Beaches" sound track, featuring Bette Midler's Grammy-winning single, "Wind 
Beneath My Wings," is on the rise again -- from No. 60 to No. 38. 
</P>
<P>
* Rapper M.C. Hammer has gotten rapped by some critics for this album, but rap 
fans seem to like it. "Please Hammer Don't Hurt 'Em" leaped from No. 69 to No. 
31. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
