<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: DEL MAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bettie Kujawa of Coronado, Gloria Parry of Del Mar and E. Allan Royster of 
Poway were reappointed Thursday to the 22nd District Agricultural Assn. by Gov. 
George Deukmejian. 
</P>
<P>
Kujawa, 66, the owner and manager of Viva Burgers -- a San Diego fast-food 
restaurant -- has served on the board since 1986. She is also a member of the 
San Diego County Hazardous Waste Management Advisory Committee. 
</P>
<P>
Parry, 67, served as the assistant livestock superintendent at the Del Mar Fair 
for 10 years until retiring in 1986. Since then, she has served on the board. 
</P>
<P>
Royster, 52, president of Royster Construction Co., has also been on the board 
since 1986. 
</P>
<P>
The three appointees' new terms expire Jan. 15, 1994. 
