<P>
USC TRACK PAIR TO COMPETE AT INDIANAPOLIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hurdler Robert Reading and long jumper Dietmar Haaf of USC will compete in the 
NCAA indoor track and field championships starting today at the Hoosier Dome in 
Indianapolis. 
</P>
<P>
Reading, the NCAA outdoor hurdles champion in 1989, has the best indoor mark in 
the 60-meter hurdles among collegians this season at 7.01 seconds. Haaf, a 
transfer from the University of Stuttgart in West Germany, tops the college 
list with a jump of 26 feet 11 3/4 inches. 
</P>
<P>
USC's Michele Taylor will compete in the women's 800 meters. UCLA's entries are 
Brian Blutreich and Tracie Millett in the men's and women's shotput, 
respectively. 
</P>
