</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
USX Holders to Vote on Icahn Plan: Takeover strategist Carl C. Icahn's proposal 
that USX Corp. spin off its steel division will be put to a vote of 
shareholders, USX said in announcing an agreement on the matter. 
</P>
<P>
In exchange for the vote, Icahn agreed not to wage a proxy fight or submit 
other matters for consideration at the steel, oil and gas giant's May 7 annual 
meeting, USX said. Stockholders will be asked whether USX should incorporate a 
separate steel business and sell at least 80% of it, Icahn said in documents 
filed with the SEC. The new company would carry no more than $1.5 billion in 
long-term debt. 
</P>
