<TEXT>
<P>
Trump Shuttle, Pilots Sign Contract: The Air Line Pilots Assn. International 
and the Trump Shuttle signed a 48-month contract. 
</P>
<P>
Ratified by the pilots union Feb. 24, it is retroactive to July, 1989, and will 
expire July 2, 1993. Company executives said it provides for wage increases for 
all 227 Trump Shuttle pilots and gives the fledgling airline the opportunity to 
use aircraft and crews more efficiently and productively. The contract also 
eliminates the two-tier wage scale for Trump Shuttle pilots. 
