<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCC TO PLAY TUESDAY IN NAIA TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Southern California College will play Washburn, Kan., in the first round of the 
National Assn. of Intercollegiate Athletics basketball tournament Tuesday at 
Kemper Arena in Kansas City, Mo. 
</P>
<P>
The Vanguards (25-8) are the 15th-seeded team in the tournament. 
</P>
<P>
Washburn, which is unseeded, is 20-11. 
</P>
<P>
If SCC wins, it will play the winner of the Philadelphia Pharmacy-Wisconsin Eau 
Claire game in the second round Thursday. Wisconsin Eau Claire is the 
second-seeded team in the 32-team tournament. 
</P>
<P>
The Vanguards defeated Christian Heritage, 90-77, in the District 3 final 
Saturday to win its first district championship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
