<TEXT>
<P>
Reckitt and Colman PLC, a British food and household goods group, has agreed to 
pay $1.25 billion for the Boyle-Midway home products unit of New York-based 
American Home Products Corp., the companies said today. 
</P>
<P>
The acquisition of Boyle-Midway, whose products include Woolite laundry soap 
and Easy-Off oven cleaner, would make Reckitt and Colman a major international 
household products manufacturer. 
</P>
<P>
Boyle-Midway is about half the size of Reckitt and Colman's household products 
and toiletries division. Boyle-Midway had $667 million in sales last year in 
the United States, Canada, France, West Germany and Spain and a pretax profit 
of $91 million, the companies said. 
