<P>
DION FAN OF HIS OLD HITS HIMSELF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
KINGSTON, N.Y. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Unlike other musicians, rock 'n' roll Hall of Famer Dion doesn't grumble when 
asked to perform his old hits. 
</P>
<P>
"I love doing old songs," said the 50-year-old Dion DiMucci, who performed this 
week as part of the "Dave Edmunds Rock 'n' Roll Revue" at the Ulster County 
Playhouse. 
</P>
<P>
"In fact, they have more value to me as time passes," he said. "And I see what 
they do to an audience. They love it. I get a big kick out of it." 
</P>
<P>
In his latest tour, Dion mixes early 1960s material like "Runaround Sue," "The 
Wanderer" and "Ruby Baby" with songs from a comeback album released last year. 
</P>
<P>
"If the song is good, it's good," he said. 
</P>
