</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
STRANDA, Norway 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The women's World Cup downhill finale, which had been rescheduled for Saturday, 
was canceled today after an overnight blizzard. 
</P>
<P>
Organizers said the race will be held next Saturday at Are, Sweden, site of the 
World Cup finals. 
</P>
<P>
After a heavy snowfall until 2 a.m. local time, the Roalden downhill course had 
up to one meter of soft snow in some places and could not be prepared for 
today's practice runs. 
